VL  - 33
IS  - 3
SP  - 463
EP  - 506
PY  - 1994
DA  - 1994/06/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(94)90040-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030439329490040X
KW  - Stochastic growth model
KW  - Analytical solution
KW  - Loglinear approximation
AB  - This paper argues that a clear understanding of the stochastic growth model can best be achieved by working out an approximate analytical solution. The proposed solution method replaces the true budget constraints and Euler equations of economic agents with loglinear approximations. The model then becomes a system of loglinear expectational difference equations, which can be solved by the method of undetermined coefficients. The paper uses this technique to study shocks to techno- logy and shocks to government spending financed by lump-sum or distortionary taxation. It emphasizes that the persistence of shocks is an important determinant of their macroeconomic effects.
